SIMPLE: personify
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Personify
<hw>Per*son"i*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Personified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Personifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[<ets>Person</ets> + <ets>-fy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>personnifier</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To regard, treat, or
represent as a person; to represent as a rational being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The poets take the liberty of <qex>personifying</qex> inanimate
things.</q> <rj><qau>Chesterfield.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be the embodiment or personification of; to
impersonate; <as>as, he <ex>personifies</ex> the law</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Personize</ent>⟦br⟧
